<item>
            <title>[LU-4796] NOT inject OBD_FAIL_FID_LOOKUP failure on dotdot entry</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4796</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The LFSCK may cannot rebuild the FID-in-dirent for &quot;..&quot; entry after the MDT restored from file-level backup, because there is not enough space in the directory head area. Then OBD_FAIL_FID_LOOKUP failed on &quot;..&quot; will cause unexpected failure. For example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;== sanity-lfsck test 5: LFSCK can handle IFIG object upgrading == 06:53:16 (1395237196)
rm: cannot remove `/mnt/lustre/d4.sanity-lfsck&apos;: Directory not empty
CMD: shadow-8vm12 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param fail_loc=0x1504
fail_loc=0x1504
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
